<link href="http://forum.neoloader.com/viewtopic.php?t=6764&amp;p=21439#p21439"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Stream file shouldn't be limited in media file and single file.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forum.neoloader.com/viewtopic.php?t=6764&amp;p=21439#p21439"><![CDATA[
<blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />Yeah but what's the benefit of doing that? Also, that's good for ed2k network only, torrent protocol doesn't have the renaming problem, plus the most spread file name sometimes is not the "original" file name. That can be discussed btw, let's see what D.X. thinks about that<br />iirc this feature is avaible in MorphXT eMule Mod, but I don't remember who coded it or the first mod that implemented that.<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />The issue is indeed mostly with ed2k only, a torrent has fixed names, I'm not sure about the dynamics of such a feature a.k.a. assuming all clients would have that how easy a small army of bots could fuck up the filenames for everyone.<br /><br />The attack vector here is to have a small quantity of clients that fakes the name on purpose and to hit a file when it just have been releases such that the small group can pose as the majority.<br /><br />If I would add it that would have to not switch automatically but offer to the user and ask for his approval.<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />You also can not have those pre-defined filters to emulate the style (Video, File, Documents, Directories, Audio, etc.)?<br /></div></blockquote><br />Not yet, but this will be added, the tree already have started/paused/stopped/complete, I will add an option in future to customize this filters.<br /><br />Also if you pres Ctrl+F you can filter a file list by keyford<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div>The option to show the countries of peers (disabled by default) with their respective flags, this is useful when'm downloading common content of my country<br /></div></blockquote><br />I already requested that feature some time ago, but keep in mind that if D.X. will add it, it will not be enabled by default because for most of the users is just a waste of cpu/memory usage. Let's see what he thinks here too, you have my +1 vote </div></blockquote><br />Lets just say that this feature is on the very bottom of my todo list <img class="smilies" src="http://forum.neoloader.com/images/smilies/biggrin.png" alt=":D" title=":D" /> if i run out of features to add or bugs to fix I will add it<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forum.neoloader.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=561">DavidXanatos</a> — Tue Jan 06, 2015 7:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
